tr.th: Non-free media information and use rationale – non-free logo for openSUSE

td.p: This is a logo owned by openSUSE Project for openSUSE distribution. It is a historical logo. Its historical usage is as follows: Modified SUSE Logo, used by openSUSE Project and distribution starting from 2005. Further details: The logo of openSUSE.
The logo is from the http://www.opensuse.org website. http://gitorious.org/opensuse/art/blobs/master/00assets/logo/official-logo-color.svg

th.style: background: #ccf; text-align: right; padding-right: 0.4em; white-space: nowrap

td.p: The entire logo is used to convey the meaning intended and avoid tarnishing or misrepresenting the intended image.

th.style: background: #ccf; text-align: right; padding-right: 0.4em; white-space: nowrap

td.p: The logo is of a size and resolution sufficient to maintain the quality intended by the company or organization, without being unnecessarily high resolution.

th.style: background: #ccf; text-align: right; padding-right: 0.4em; white-space: nowrap

td.p: The image is used to identify openSUSE distribution, a notable product or service. The significance of the logo is to help the reader identify the product or service, assure the readers that they have reached the right article containing critical commentary about that product or service, and illustrate branding associations of the product or service in a way that words alone could not convey.

td.p:
SVG uploaded by Charles E. Keisler, any questions, please ask me on my talk page.
If your image has been replaced with this, and you don't understand how an SVG image is preferential, please ask.

Due to the nature of my mass SVG creation, I often don't know the context of what I am adding.
If this image is not correct in any way, do not hesitate to remove it from the article.
In such a situation, please notify me.

tr.td: This is a retouched picture, which means that it has been digitally altered from its original version. Some of the modifications are: Converted from raster to vector by finding a common artwork source (.AI, .SVG, .PDF, .EPS, .PS). Edits by Koman90.
